articles.description: Clemson junior guard Shelton Mitchell is out of the hospital but remains in the concussion protocol following an injury suffered during Wednesday's loss to Florida State.
articles.headline: Clemson's Shelton Mitchell exits hospital after hit to head

articles.description: Mark Schlabach joins OTL to discuss the news that a U.S. District Court denied a motion to dismiss federal criminal charges against three of the 10 men arrested for their alleged roles in the FBI's two-year investigation into college basketball corruption
articles.headline: Court denies dismissal off CBB probe

articles.description: Reggie Lynch maintains his innocence against sexual misconduct allegations but has dropped appeals of his Minnesota expulsion because he does not feel he could receive a fair hearing.
articles.headline: Reggie Lynch drops appeals of sexual misconduct rulings, accepts expulsion

articles.description: A U.S. District Court judge denied a motion Thursday to dismiss federal criminal charges against former Adidas executives James Gatto and Merl Code and former sports agent Christian Dawkins in the FBI's investigation into college basketball corruption.
articles.headline: Judge denies motion to drop charges in corruption case against ex-Adidas execs, agent

articles.description: With Kentucky missing an edge, along with a couple of pieces, could the reeling Wildcats miss the NCAA tourney for the second time under John Calipari?

articles.description: Have Oklahoma's recent troubles made Trae Young not a sure thing for the Wooden Award? Arizona's Deandre Ayton is among the players who might get another look.
articles.headline: Wooden Watch: Can someone catch Trae Young?

images.name: Greenberg would take Sexton over Young for NBA

videos.description: On the first possession of the game, Jordan Bowden gets a steal and then finishes with a slam for the Vols.
videos.headline: Tennessee starts off with steal and dunk from Bowden

videos.description: Kyle Alexander grabs an offensive board and then slams it down with one hand for the Vols.
videos.headline: Alexander throws down hammer dunk

videos.description: Grant Williams steps around his defender and makes a jumper for Tennessee.
videos.headline: Williams works around defender for bucket

videos.description: Theo Pinson drives to the basket and draws contact on the lay-in to get a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Pinson makes tough and-1 for UNC

videos.description: UNC gets a stop and Sterling Manley quickly gets the ball on the other end and finishes with a slam.
videos.headline: Manley beats defender on dunk

videos.description: Kenny Williams snags an offensive rebound and puts it back in to cut the Vols' lead.
videos.headline: Williams comes through with putback bucket

videos.description: Theo Pinson steals the ball and bounces a pass to Luke Maye who finishes with a dunk for UNC.
videos.headline: Pinson steal sets up Maye dunk

videos.description: UNC gets an offensive rebound and Joel Berry II sinks a 3-pointer to put the Tar Heels in the lead.
videos.headline: Berry's 3-pointer gives North Carolina momentum

videos.description: Jordan Bone gets an offensive rebound and passes it to Jordan Bowden who makes a long 3-pointer for the Vols.
videos.headline: Tennessee fired up after Bowden 3-pointer

videos.description: Grant Williams gets an aggressive driving layup to extend Tennessee's lead late against No. 7 North Carolina.
videos.headline: Williams extends Vols' lead on lay-in

videos.description: Theo Pinson passes to Kenny Williams who drains the a 3-pointer to give UNC the lead.
videos.headline: UNC answers with Williams' 3-pointer

videos.description: The Vols aren't able to hold on late against the Heels as they fall to 7-2 on the season.
videos.headline: No. 20 Tennessee falls to No. 7 UNC 78-73
